# godMCP - MCP Server Creator and Manager

[![Python 3.10+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![FastMCP](https://img.shields.io/badge/FastMCP-2.13+-green.svg)](https://github.com/jlowin/fastmcp)
[![MCP](https://img.shields.io/badge/MCP-Compatible-purple.svg)](https://modelcontextprotocol.io)

**godMCP** is a powerful Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that enables you to create, manage, and deploy custom MCP servers with ease. Think of it as a meta-server that helps you build other MCP servers.

> üéØ **Perfect for:** AI developers, automation enthusiasts, and anyone who wants to extend their MCP-enabled tools with custom functionality.

## Features

- üöÄ **Create MCP Servers** - Generate complete, production-ready MCP servers with custom tools
- üîß **Tool Implementation** - Provide full implementations or stubs for incremental development
- üìù **Configuration Management** - Automatically register servers in your MCP configuration
- üîÑ **Update Tools** - Modify tool implementations after server creation
- üéØ **Multi-Client Support** - Works with Kiro, Claude Desktop, Cursor, and other MCP clients
- ‚úÖ **Proper Indentation** - Generates syntactically correct Python code
- üåç **Environment-Based Config** - Explicit control over where servers are registered

